description.narrative: This activity (Democratic Institutions Support Programme(DIALOGO)) is a component of Democratic Governance Support Programme(DIALOGO) reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Procurement of Services' and a budget of £9,468,369. This component benefits Mozambique, and works in the following sector(s): Decentralisation and support to subnational government, Democratic participation and civil society, Elections, Media and free flow of information, Human rights, Women's equality organisations and institutions. , with the following implementing partners: DAI Europe. The start date is 01-03-2011 and the end date is 31-12-2017.
